09/04/2007
PODGORICA, Montenegro -- Barbara Prammer, speaker of the Austrian Parliament's National Council (lower house), says her country backs Montenegro's EU accession.
During a visit to Podgorica on Friday (April 6th), Prammer met with counterpart Ranko Krivokapic, President Filip Vujanovic, Prime Minister Zeljko Sturanovic and Foreign Minister Milan Rocen.
They focused on boosting bilateral ties, particularly as regards co-operation in the economic, energy and banking sectors, tourism, environmental protection and road infrastructure.
Austria plans to provide 650,000 euros in assistance to Montenegro's Parliament this year.
(Pobjeda, Vijesti - 07/04/07;
RTCG - 06/04/07)
